ciscoLwappDownloadMIB.name: ciscoLwappDownloadMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoLwappDownloadMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS Email: cs-wnbu-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoLwappDownloadMIB.description: This MIB is intended to be implemented on all those devices operating as Central controllers, that terminate the Light Weight Access Point Protocol tunnel from Cisco Light-weight LWAPP Access Points. The relationship between the controller and the LWAPP APs is depicted as follows. A measure of the quality of the signal relative to the strength of noise expressed in 'dB'. REFERENCE [1] Wireless LAN Medium Access Control ( MAC ) and Physical Layer ( PHY ) Specifications. [2] Draft-obara-capwap-lwapp-00.txt, IETF Light Weight Access Point Protocol

clDLApBootTable.name: clDLApBootTable
clDLApBootTable.description: This table represents primary and backup version of a a mesh AP. An entry in this table gets added when a mesh AP associates to the controller and entry gets removed when mesh AP disassociates from the controller.

cldlApBootEntry.name: cldlApBootEntry
cldlApBootEntry.description: An (conceptual) entry in this table represents version information for a AP.

cldlAPName.name: cldlAPName
cldlAPName.description: This object represents the name of the AP.

cldlAPPrimaryVersion.name: cldlAPPrimaryVersion
cldlAPPrimaryVersion.description: This object represents the primary image version of the AP.

cldlAPBackupVersion.name: cldlAPBackupVersion
cldlAPBackupVersion.description: This object represents the backup image version of the AP.

cldlAPSwapImage.name: cldlAPSwapImage
cldlAPSwapImage.description: This object is used to swap the AP image. true : swaps the image of AP. false: do not swaps the image of AP.

cldlApDownloadImage.name: cldlApDownloadImage
cldlApDownloadImage.description: This object is used to configure the image. primary : Downloads primary image from the controller. backup : Downloads backup image from the controller.

clDLResetTable.name: clDLResetTable
clDLResetTable.description: This table used to reset the WLC and AP. User resets WLC by adding a row to this table through explicit management action from the network manager. A row is created by specifying clResetTime, or clResetDate and clResetTime setting the RowStatus object to 'createAndGo'.

cldlResetEntry.name: cldlResetEntry
cldlResetEntry.description: An (conceptual) entry in this table used to reset the WLC and AP.

cldlResetIndex.name: cldlResetIndex
cldlResetIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies one instance of sheduled reset vector of the controller.

cldlResetDateAndTime.name: cldlResetDateAndTime
cldlResetDateAndTime.description: This object used to schedule the future reset time of the controller. Format: MM/DD/YY:HH/MM/SS.

cldlResetSwapImage.name: cldlResetSwapImage
cldlResetSwapImage.description: This object used to select the image to be loaded after reset.

cldlResetAP.name: cldlResetAP
cldlResetAP.description: This object is used to reset all the APs associate to the controller. true : resets all the APs. false : do not resets the APs.

cldlResetRowStatus.name: cldlResetRowStatus
cldlResetRowStatus.description: This object is the status column used for creating and deleting instances of the columnar objects in this table. destory : will clear the reset. The following object is mandatory for successful creation of an entry: clResetDateAndTime.

cldlResetSaveConfig.name: cldlResetSaveConfig
cldlResetSaveConfig.description: This object is used to save the configuration before rebooting the controller. true : save and resets the controller. false : resets the controller with out saving configuration.

cldlResetAlertTime.name: cldlResetAlertTime
cldlResetAlertTime.description: This object is used to specify the number of seconds before the scheduled reset at which the trap message will be generated.

ciscoLwappScheduledResetNotif.name: ciscoLwappScheduledResetNotif
ciscoLwappScheduledResetNotif.description: This notification is generated if we scheduled the status and controller is going to reboot.

ciscoLwappResetFailedNotif.name: ciscoLwappResetFailedNotif
ciscoLwappResetFailedNotif.description: This notification is generated if we failed to schedule reset.

ciscoLwappClearResetNotif.name: ciscoLwappClearResetNotif
ciscoLwappClearResetNotif.description: This notification is generated if we cancelled the scheduled reset.

ciscoLwappDownloadMIBCompliance.name: ciscoLwappDownloadMIBCompliance
ciscoLwappDownloadMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement the ciscoLwappDownloadMIB module.

ciscoLwappDLApGroup.name: ciscoLwappDLApGroup
ciscoLwappDLApGroup.description: This collection of objects represents the information about the general attributes and functional parameters of those APs that have joined the controller.

ciscoLwappDLResetGroup.name: ciscoLwappDLResetGroup
ciscoLwappDLResetGroup.description: This collection of objects represents the information about scheduled reset date and time of the controller.

ciscoLwappDLNotifsGroup.name: ciscoLwappDLNotifsGroup
ciscoLwappDLNotifsGroup.description: This supplemental collection of objects represents the shecduled reset related notifications sent by the agent to a network management station.
